  "intent": "Explain how regin loads, dispatches, and executes lint/rewrite rules: the engine-agnostic Protocol, the three-source registry precedence (explicit settings \u2192 legacy grit fallback \u2192 autodiscovered bundles), the three concrete adapters (Grit, Bundle, Radon), the PostToolUse hook that drives them per edit, the two in-tree example bundles under example/rule/, and the step-by-step playbook for adding a new engine. Use this when adding a new engine kind, packaging a new rule pack as a bundle, wiring an existing engine into a new language, importing one of the example bundles, or debugging why a rule fired (or didn't) on a file.",
